<br>
Like I have said before, I have my right to say exactly how I feel.  Yes I think Tallas is an immature Brat - and I think LOTD is mostly, in MY opinion, a bunch of shit 60's thrown together.  Just goes to show that numbers will not win out an encounter. <br>
<br>
As for my experience with the game, very contrary to what Ganamil said, I have seen ALL of the game.  Every single zone, and been a part of a lot of killing.  <br>
<br>
Before I left the game, I was on an entirely different server, which good friends of mine know of a guild I belong to on that server.  I have seen the highest ends of the game, been there and done that.  Why do you think I was so pissed off when the Sleepers incident happened?  (No I was not a member of Conquest).  But quite honestly, knowing what my guild was working so hard for, only to see a broken script and a bugged Kerafym (The Sleeper once awakened for those that do not know), as well as watching other guilds try so hard to be able to complete card quests in POM when the Vendor selling the combiner to actually DO the quests wasn't even in place in Rivervale for 3 months AFTER Velious.  <br>
<br>
Than watch as Verant staff, Hell even a developer, very misinformed, told my guild directly on that server that Sleepers does work as intended, and that the following is what happened. <br>
<br>
1&gt; Cloth caps are supposed to be in the zone falling off the warders.   <br>
 False:   Cloth caps are falling off the warders right now because Verant has not itemized the common and uncommon drops - and Cloth caps are what the default is to drop in place of those items when not in the database. <br>
<br>
2&gt; The Human form of the sleeper was a direct result of Velious not patching.  <br>
<br>
SO FALSE: Of course the reason for this is the old model looked similar to Trakanon.  They are updating the model of the &quot;Live&quot; Sleeper and the reason for the human form is because it is not finished yet or in the zone model database. <br>
And I knew this all the while, when Verant was telling every single player out there that the screenshot taker forgot to patch Velious - when the last time there was a sleeper patch was when they originally got around to changing the model of the sleeping sleeper. <br>
<br>
3&gt; POM Nuff said about this. <br>
<br>
So Yes Ganamil, I have been to these zones, I have worked ever so hard on Characters not only on this server but another. Only to have Verant's lack of respect... And as far as putting more time into &quot;Completing&quot; what is viewed as the end encounter in Everquest at this time, when it isn't even fucking finished after 6 months Velious  has been out, is not only a waste of my gaming time, but others that have worked their tails off to beat the unbeatable game.  Yes, there is an end to Everquest.  While be it subjective, my end with Everquest was seeing everything the game had to offer, get the best equipment for the guild as a whole to take down the toughest mobs in the game, and witness what was supposed to be one of the coolest events in Everquest history with the slaying of the live sleeper.  <br>
<br>
But I digress. <br>
<br>
In the meantime, if someone asks me the opinion of a player, or I see the need to let off some steam about my occurance with another player and their immature actions, hell yeah I am going to write about it.  Its what these forums are for right?  What the hell makes me different than ANY of you?  Just because I can look at a user base and modify shitty posters to make sure they do not come back?  <br>
<br>
And power trips??  My god.  This is a FUCKING game. NOTHING to do with real life.  Once some of you realize that and can enjoy the game and the boards for what they are, ENTERTAINMENT, than maybe the people coming here and saying I am a shit admin might lighten up, and have a nice warm glass of shut the hell up. <br>
<br>
But damn tootin'.  If someone ruins the entertainment with their actions whether it be here or in the game; I care about people I have never even fucking met, nor ever will - and I want to see them have the experience and fun that they so desire out of this game, without having to deal with the Tallas's of the world.   Idiots and shit players are ruining everquest at this point in time.  And I hate to say it, but it may be a downfall of MMORPG's as a whole.  The more the game is out and known, the more and more quality experienced players leave, and others replace them.  <br>
<br>
See ya Ganamil - I am going to go plan a raid with the ghoul lord. <br>
<br>
